==================================================================================================================================Lesson 1 = Daily Life: Page 54-63
Practice: 1)A) 1)Takeshi San -> Takeshi san nihonjin desu 2)Sora san -> Sora san wa kankokujin desu 3)robaato san -> robaaton san wa igirisujin desu
  4)Yamashita sensei -> Yamashita sensei wa nihonjin desu
B)1) Takeshi san -> Takeshi san wa yonensee desu 2)sora san -> sora san wa sannensee desu 3)robaato san -> robaato san wa yonnensee desu 
C)1) Takeshi san -> takeshi san wa nijunisai desu 2)sora san wa -> sora san wa hatachi desu 3)robaato san -> robaato san wa nijinisai desu
  4) yamashite sensei wa yonjunanasai desu
D)Tell your group (1) your name, (2) your nationality, (3) your year in school (4)your age
  watashi wa temesu shoon desu, kanada desu, zero nensei desu, san ju sansai desu
2)A)listening-Q&A corrections
B)(A) listening-asking about age =nansai desu ka(B)asking about year in school=nannensee desu ka (C)listening-asking about maeris family
3)A) Translate the following phrases into Japanese using no:
1)My Teacher = Watashi no sensei 2)My telephone number = Watashi no denwa bangou 3)My name = Watashi no namae 4)Takeshis major = Takeshi san no senkou 
  5)Marys friend = Maeri san no tomodachi 6) Student at university of london = london daigaku no gakusee 7)Teacher of japanese language = nihongo no sensee
  8)High school teacher = koukou no sensei 
B)Look at the chart and describe each person given the cues:
A) Schools:
  1)Takeshi san wa Sakura daigaku no gakusee desu 2)Sora san wa Seoul daigaku no gakusee desu 
  3) Robaato san wa London daigaku no gakusee desu 4)Yamashite wa Sakura daigaku no sensei desu
B) Majors:
1)Takeshi san no senkoo wa rekishi desu 2)Sora san no senkoo wa konpyuutaa desu 3)Robaato san no senkoo wa bijinesu desu
C) Listen and answer questions
D)Group work
4)A)Pair work = Telephone Numbers: Denwa bangou wa nanban desu ka?
  B) Group work =  Ask others their telephone numbers
5) Time = Look at clock and say time:
  A)1)3=SanJi desu 2)9=KyuJi desu 3)11=JuIchiJi desu 4)7=ShichiJi desu 5)2:30=nijihan desu 6)4:30=yojihan desu 7)12=juniji desu 8)6=rokuji desu 
  B)Pair work=Asking what time it is: Ima nanji desu ka?
  C)Look at the map and answer questions(time in city): TooKyoo Wa, ima nanji desu ka?
6)A)Review Exercies:
Onamae wa? = What is your name
GoShuusshin wa? = Where do you come from?
Oshigoto wa? = What is your occupation?
Nannensee desu ka? = what year of school?
Nansai desu ka? =  how old are you?
Senkoo wa? = What is your school major?
B)Groupwork = Roleplay with students and fill out their information
C) Group work = create a Self Introduction and say to class

==================================================================================================================================Lesson 2 = Shopping: Page 75-88
1)A) Read the numbers: A) 34 = san juu yon B)67 = roku juu nana C)83 = hachi juu san D)99 = kyuu juu kyuu E)125 = hyaku ni juu go F)515 = go hyaku juu go
  G)603 = roppyaku san H) 850 = happyaku go juu I)1,300 = sen san byaku J)3,400 = san zen yon hyaku K)8,900 = hassen kyuu byaku L)35,000 = san man go sen 
  M)64,500 = rokuman yon sen go hyaku  N)92,340 = kyuu man ni sen san hyaku yon juu
B)Look at each picture and listen to how much each costs: 1)no-to(notebook) = 450(yon hyaku go ju en) 2)kasa(umbrella) = 1,000(sen en) 
  3)shinbun(newspaper) = 160(hyaku roku juu en) 4)hon(book) = 1500(sen go hyaku en) 5)kutsu(shoes) = 3,500(san zen go hyaku) 6)tokee(watch) = 10,000(ichiman en)
  7)kaban(bag) = 20,000(ni man en) 8)saifu(wallet) = 8,000(ha sen en) 9)Ji-nsu(jeans) = 9,000(kyuu sen en) 10)jidensha(bicycle) = 25,000 (ni man go sen en)
  11)sumaho(smartphone) = 34,000 (san man yon sen en)12)boushi(hat) = 2,800(ni sen happyaku en)
C)Pair work: one looks at picture and asks how much (noun wa ikura desu ka):
2)A)Pair work: Kore and sore: items 1-6 are near you(kore), 7-12 are near your friend(sore). Kore wa nan desu ka(what's this) vs sore wa nan desu ka(whats that)
B)Look at each building and say what each building is: are wa nan desu ka? (what is that(over there))
  Toshokan(library), 1) are wa Daigaku desu(university), Ginkou(bank), yubinkyouku(post office), konbini(convenience store)
C)Pair work: point x5 things out in classroom and ask your partner what they are using kore and sore
3)A)look at the pictures and make sentences using kono, sono, and ano:
  1)sono pen wa ni hyaku kyuu ju en desu 2)ano konpyuutaa wa roku man ha sen en desu 3)sono saifu wa yon sen san hyaku en desu 4)kono hon wa san sen go hyaku en desu
  5)ano jidensha wa ichi man nana sen en desu
B)pair work: ask and answer questions on how expensive each item is using kono sono and ano:kono noun wa ikura desu ka?
C)pair work: steal his look: point out items your partner has and ask him how much the cost:
4)look at the pictures and answer where the locations are: doko, koko, soko, asoko






